gomodel:SYNGO_1503  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Patch-clamp measurements of Kir6.2 channels overexpressed in HEK cells.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has ATP-gated ion channel activity and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (show with high-resolution technique). The inference to term 'ATP-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential' is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P70673] SyNGO ID 1500 (PMID:17883401, EM). Experimental description: Molecular biology. Using oligonucleotide primers and standard PCR methods, we engineered two parental plasmids encoding human Kir6.1 and human Kir6.2 (in pECE)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_1503" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

